1 (a) “Civil rights or employment laws” means any state or
2 federal law which prohibits discrimination because of race, creed,
3 color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or
4 expression, age or disability. The term includes, without
5 limitation:
6 (1) Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 42 U.S.C. §§
7 2000e et seq.;
8 (2) The Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1967, 29
9 U.S.C. §§ 621-634;
10 (3) The Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, 42 U.S.C.
11 §§ 12101 et seq.; and
12 (4) NRS 613.310 to 613.4383, inclusive.
13 (b) “State money” does not include money which is received by
14 this State from the Federal Government for distribution and use in
15 this State pursuant to federal law or federal regulation.
